      "note_no": "29",
      "note": "The phrase lam yastati tawlan is often taken to mean \"he is not in a position to afford\", i.e., in the financial sense; but Muhammad Abduh very convincingly expresses the view that it applies to all manner of preventive circumstances, be they of a material, personal or social nature (Manar V, 19)."
